history.content:
hello, I'm looking a bit ahead, after Fall 2019 I'll have 6 classes left to graduate with double major CS/DS (all technicals).  I could try and fit things to graduate in 2020, but most likely I'll probably just take 3 classes each in Spring 2019 and Fall 2020.  However, I probably will want to take a 4th class in each semester, probably for P/NP purposes.  No industry preferences at the moment except software and data-related.

So my question is this:  what classes are good for P/NP?  To me, ideally the class would be 1) helpful and useful for industry 2) a class that is not project based. (I tend to do better with project-based classes as opposed to classes where a large percentage is based on exams) and of course 3) hard to get a really good grade without putting in tons of work

My list of remaining for 2020 (open to suggestions as well). 6 of the courses I'll need to take for a grade.:

CS 188 (will be required for DS so can't take this P/NP)

CS 189 and/or STAT 102 (one of these will be required for DS)

CS 161

CS 162

CS 164

CS 169

CS 186

INFO 154

TIA!
